Comment: .The opening resulted in a very closed game, were both sides avoided exchanges, until black decide for a centre pawn break with 11...d5 and after white's move decided to precipitate the action by exchanging the pawns, then instead of dealing with white threats (black had a pawn hanging and a knight pinned), black decided for an unneeded move 13.h6 after which white took the initiative and due to a cramped camp by black with lack of connection between pieces, white went on to win the game.
